<br>
Lets face it. We can only speculate on what will happen on these &quot;Legends&quot; servers. But lets keep a few things in mind...<br>
<br>
1. Very Liberal Transfer policy will mean alot of high levels right away. If folks were upset about people getting to high levels quickly on FV, how will they react to &quot;instant&quot; high levels?<br>
<br>
2. Dynamic Quests on Legends maybe more plentiful, but frankly they will most likely be resolved / won by the uber guilds. Why? Simply because they have the most resources available to accomplish these dynamic quests. For example,  a dragon spawns in Lesser Fay.. word hits the streets, 3 groups from uber guild &quot;A&quot; will port into steamfont or Greaterfay, all 50+, all within 10 minutes of hearing about it. How will this make the &quot;Roleplayers&quot; feel? Pretty left out I imagine.<br>
<br>
3. New items released on Legends servers before (not exclusive to) regular servers will only entice power gamers to move to legends... especially with a chance to have an item named after you. What power gamer wouldnt want that?<br>
<br>
4. No TLC. A good number of folks on FV seem to really like TLC (dont get me started). Nuff said.<br>
<br>
5. While the little extras like the map and character page are nice... thats all they are. They do not enhance the game mechanics and its arguable whether or not they will enhance game play. If folks really wanted to tell their stories they would use already exsisting boards like these (Itchy's monday stories for example). Ten to one says most folks won't care about these little &quot;add ons&quot; in a month or two and will just stick to Linux boxes and sniffers for there &quot;enhanced&quot; game play experience.<br>
<br>
So, roleplayers... I would really think twice about visiting there but thats just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Now with all that said, I must confess that I actually submitted a feedback a year ago for a &quot;premium&quot; server. However, my request was for a premium server with better CS available, an age restriction (hard to enforce obviously but I wanted to see it tried at least), and a population cap of 1800. I would pay extra money for better CS (more GM's with more leeway to help players). I really would. I would find value in a population cap and even though I know age has nothing to do with maturity I do think there is some sense in having an age restriction. <br>
<br>
Thats worth 40 bucks US a month to me.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
